  "prompt": "Do Indians celebrate Christmas?",
  "response": "Yes, many Indians celebrate Christmas. India is a diverse country with people practicing various religions, including Christianity. Although Christians make up a minority of the population, Christmas is celebrated with great enthusiasm in places with significant Christian communities. You can find vibrant festivities, decorations, special church services, and public and private celebrations in states like Kerala, Goa, and parts of northeastern India. Additionally, Christmas is recognized as a public holiday across the country, and many people of different faiths participate in the celebrations by sharing greetings, sweets, and enjoying the festive atmosphere.",
